Preheat your #oven{} to 210°C. Pop the @sweet potato fries{250%g} and @British Hickory Smoked Sausages{2} on a #baking tray{}. Drizzle the fries with @olive oil{1%tbsp} and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Toss to coat then spread out and roast on the top shelf of your oven until golden and the sausages are cooked, ~{18-20%minutes}.

> The sausages are cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of oil in a #small saucepan{} on medium-high heat. Add the @British Smoked Bacon Lardons{60%g} and cook, stirring occasionally, until crisp and golden, ~{6-7%minutes}. Stir in the @onion marmalade{40%g}, @sugar{1%tsp} and @water{1%tbsp}. Bubble until thickened and jammy, ~{2-3%minutes}, then set aside.

Meanwhile, trim the root from the @baby gem lettuce{1} and separate the leaves. In a #large bowl{}, mix the @red wine vinegar{6%tbsp} with olive oil (see ingredients for amount).

1 minute before the fries and sausages are ready, warm the @brioche hot dog buns{2} in the oven for ~{1%minute}. Meanwhile, add the baby gem to the bowl with the dressing. Toss to coat.

Once the sausages are cooked, slice the brioche hot dog bun down the middle. Pop a sausage in the bun then spoon over the bacon jam.

Serve alongside the sweet potato fries and baby gem salad. Enjoy!